{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we applied a selection on whether sources have a non-zero shape measurement weight:AlphaRecalC_weight > 0.",
    "(39)This selection is highly correlated with the resolution selection, but can only be applied after the resolution selection has been applied (because the resolution selection is invoked in the weight recalibration, Sect. 7.1.2).",
    "Similarly, because of the weight recalibration, the weight selection can only be applied to the subset of the data that also satisfy the resolution selection, and so it is not meaningful to quote the fraction of the MASK ≤ 1 dataset that satisfy the weight requirement.",
    "Furthermore, as can be seen in Fig. 29, these are primarily faint sources.",
    "Of the currently available dataset, the weight selection removes the 13.85% of the sources."
  ]
}